xyz.thepathfinder.android

Class Transport

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.thepathfinder.android.Listenable<E>
      • xyz.thepathfinder.android.Model<E>
        • xyz.thepathfinder.android.SubscribableModel<E>
          • xyz.thepathfinder.android.SubscribableCrudModel<TransportListener>
            • xyz.thepathfinder.android.Transport

  • public class Transport
extends SubscribableCrudModel<TransportListener>
    Interface to the Pathfinder server's transport API. A transport may be create by a Cluster object with the Cluster.createTransport(String, double, double, TransportStatus, JsonObject) method.

    Be careful with the update methods, they do not update the object immediately. They send the updates to the pathfinder server. If the server responds the transport's fields will then be updated. To listen for updates add a TransportListener.

    See Also:
    Cluster, TransportListener, TransportStatus

      • getInstance

        public static Transport getInstance(String path,
                    PathfinderServices services)
        Returns an instance of a transport model. If the transport is in the model registry, it will return that transport. If the transport is not in the model registry a new transport with default values will be created.
        Parameters:
        path - of the model.
        services - a pathfinder services object.
        Returns:
        a transport.

      • getInstance

        protected static Transport getInstance(JsonObject transportJson,
                    PathfinderServices services)
        Returns an instance of a transport model. If the transport is in the model registry, it will return that transport. It will call update notifications for all changes to the transport.
        Parameters:
        transportJson - JSON that represents the transport.
        services - a pathfinder services object.
        Returns:
        a transport.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the JSON doesn't represent a transport.
